article_summaries: The 2023 Sundance Film Festival kicked off on Thursday, January 19 and ends on Sunday, January 29 in Park City, Utah. It was the first in-person festival since 2020 and was filled with movie premieres, red carpet events and mixers for celebrities. Dakota Johnson, Anne Hathaway and more stars took over the event with their stylish ensembles.

Cory Doctorow explains how platforms die. He says platforms are good to their users, then abuse their users to make things better for their business customers, and then abuse those business customers to claw back all the value for themselves.

The Bulletin of Atomic Scientists moved the hands of the symbolic clock 10 seconds forward to 90 seconds to midnight on Tuesday. It is the closest the clock has been to symbolic doom since it was created more than 75 years ago. The organization is hoping the clock will be a wake-up call for world leaders and the public.

Antonio Banderas is best known for voicing the animated character Puss in Boots since 2004's Shrek 2. He has voiced the character in five films and two TV specials. Antonio had a problem with his vocal cords during the first Puss In Boots movie because he was singing on Broadway. He had a heart attack six years ago.

Skipping exercise in favor of less demanding activities can affect memory and thinking abilities. The Department of Health and Human Services recommends adults engage in at least 150 minutes of moderate to intense physical activity each week.
On February 1 and 2, a rare green comet will pass by Earth for the first time in 50,000 years. The best chance to see it will be on February 1 when it's closest to the Earth.

ABC debuted the new season of The Bachelor on Monday night. Zach Shallcross, 26, is the new Bachelor. He sent 10 women home on the first night, the most in 12 years. Rolling Stone critic Andrea Marks fell asleep during the premiere.
Jocelyn Delk Adams shares her go-to warm winter meals. Her rotisserie chicken stuffed shells and lemony chicken and rice casserole are her favorite recipes.

RxPass is a prescription drug discount program for Prime members. It will cost $5 a month to fill as many prescriptions as they need from a list of about 50 generic medications. The program is available in 42 states and Washington, D.C. at launch.
Daniel Jones is a free agent at the end of the season. General manager Joe Schoen would like to have Daniel Jones back next season. Daniel played well this season.

The Dow Jones Industrial Average, the S&P 500 and the Nasdaq were trading lower on Tuesday. On Monday, the Dow rose 254 points. The Nasdaq is up 8.6% for the year but down 29.2% from its November 2021 record high. The S&p 500 is up 3.1% over the last two days. The index is up 4.7% this year.
Kings use early 3-pointers, big 4th quarter to top Grizzlies 133-100. Domantas Sabonis had his sixth triple-double of the season. Memphis has lost three straight after an 11-game winning streak.

A threat actor stole encrypted backups and an encryption key for a portion of GoTo-owned data during a data breach. The breach also affected GoTo's LastPass affiliate. GoTo plans to reset the passwords of affected users and reauthorize MFA settings where applicable.

The 14th annual Elma Winter Wine Festival kicked off on Saturday, Jan. 21. The festival featured over 20 wineries, a variety of crafts and food vendors, a beer garden, a silent auction, and live music presentations from Backfire Band, Joker’s Wild and The Olson Brothers.

Julie Turner will be the new special envoy for human rights in North Korea. The position has been vacant since January 2017. It was created by a 2004 law to draw attention to human rights issues in North Korean.

Ansel Elgort and Shailene Woodley have been on vacation in Italy together. They have been friends since they starred in The Fault in Our Stars and the Divergent franchise together. Ansel has been accused of sexually assaulting a 17-year-old girl.

The stars were out in force for the Chanel show at the Grand Palais Éphémère during Paris Fashion Week on Tuesday. Roger Federer and his wife Mirka were on the front row with Anna Wintour and Australian film director Baz Luhrmann.

Nickel Creek have released a new album called Celebrants. It's the follow-up to Chris Thile, Sean Watkins, and Sara Watkins’ 2014 release A Dotted Line. Eric Valentine, who's worked with Queens of the Stone Age and Grace Potter, produced the album. The album's first single is “Strangers,” which describes the awkwardness of meeting a long-lost friend after some time. Nickel Creek will play three shows at Nashville’s Ryman Auditorium on April 27, 28, and 29.

Josephine Baker, the American-born French Black star and civil rights activist was a huge inspiration behind Dior's Haute Couture Spring 23 collection. Maria Garzia Chiuri collaborates with Chanakya School of Craft for the scenography of the show.

Abigail Kinoiki Kekaulike Kawānanakoa died on Dec. 11, 2022 at the age of 96. More than 1,600 people came to Iolani Palace on Sunday to pay their respects to the Campbell estate heiress. She was the great grand-niece of the last Hawaiian King David Kalākaua. A private funeral service will be held at the Royal Mausoleum at Mauna ʻAla on Monday at 1:30 p.m.
Pop culture queen Bevy Smith gives a talk packed with wry wisdom about authenticity, confidence and success.

Malaysia Airlines has joined the United Nations Global Compact (UNGC). UNGC is an initiative that promotes sustainable aviation practices. United Airlines, Singapore Airlines, Japan Airlines, Ryanair, and Air France-KLM are other airlines that have joined the UNGC. Malaysia Airlines launched its Sustainability Blueprint in April 2021.

Pagcor says there have been no criminal activities concerning the industry of offshore gaming operations for over three months. Senator Sherwin Gatchalian recently called the government-owned gaming regulator out in a Senate hearing for its failure to address the illegal activities of Philippine offshore gaming operators (Pogos).

SpaceX has completed the first-ever wet dress rehearsal of its stacked Super Heavy rocket and Starship spacecraft. The rehearsal took place at SpaceX’s Starbase facility in Boca Chica, Texas, on Monday. The exercise is an important step toward the vehicle’'s first orbital test flight, which could take place in February or March.

There was a 24-hour power outage in Pakistan on Monday. The country's overburdened electrical system collapsed, leading to a rolling wave of blackouts. The economic crisis in Pakistan is getting worse. The government is under pressure to pay long-standing debts.

Maya Jama took over the role of Love Island host from Laura Whitmore. The new season kicked off last week and the first episode of Aftersun was watched by 1.82 million people, compared to 1.51 million watching Love Island. Maya has been given 50 percent more airtime than Laura.

In March 2011 Erskine Bowles and Alan Simpson warned about U.S. government debt. They warned that a fiscal crisis could be expected within two years. Not much was done to reduce the deficits. The interest rate on 10-year U.s. bonds was about 3.5 percent at the time. Now it's about 3%.

Two teenagers were shot and killed at an alternative educational program in Des Moines, Iowa. Preston Walls, 18, of Des Moines was charged with two counts of murder and one count of attempted murder. William Holmes, 49, the founder of the program, was seriously injured and in surgery.

U.S. crude oil for March delivery fell 2 cents to $81.62 a barrel Monday. Brent crude rose 56 cents to  $88.19 a barrel. Wholesale gasoline for February delivery rose 5 cents, heating oil rose 8 cents, natural gas rose 27 cents. Gold for February deliveries rose 40 cents to$1,928.60 an ounce, silver fell 38 cents, copper was flat at $4.26 a pound and the euro fell to $1.0859.

RxPass is a new add-on for Prime members. It will allow Prime members to get as many drugs as they need from a list of 50 generic medications to treat more than 80 common chronic conditions. The service costs $5 a month per person and delivery is free. Amazon has pushed deeper into health care in recent years. The company launched its own online pharmacy in 2020.

Sophie Monk has made her own version of Miley Cyrus' hit song, Flowers. She dressed up in a gold outfit similar to the one Miley wears in the music video and danced her heart out. The 'dress' was made out of metallic wrapping paper and a table runner. Sophie's husband, Joshua Gross, filmed the video. The couple eloped at their home on the NSW Central Coast in March 2022.

Abbie Chatfield has a three-month dating rule for 2023. She split from her ex Konrad Bień-Stephen in September after a year of being in an open relationship. Abbie is dating casually but she doesn't want a relationship.

Bob McGrath died peacefully at home surrounded by his family. He was one of the longest-standing human actors on 'Sesame Street' and a recurring cast member for 47 seasons. Bob's last episode on the show was 'Having a Ball' in 2017.
Microsoft is experimenting with a new feature in the Edge browser that allows you to view and interact with two tabs side-by-side.
A man suspected of killing at least 11 people and wounding nine others in a mass shooting in Monterey Park, California, late Saturday fatally shot himself.

Amy Boyes' daughter Madeline was born 16 weeks premature. Madeline didn't talk until she was two. She spent time with a speech therapist who worked with her to improve Madeline's speech. Amy is grateful that Madeline is talking.

There was a risk-on move for equities on Monday. The Nasdaq Composite was up 2.01%, the Philadelphia Semiconductor Index up 5.01% and all 11 sector-select SPDR ETFs were in the green. The S&P 500 gained 1.19%. Advanced Micro Devices ( AMD) was the top-performing stock in the S-P 500, with Western Digital ( WDC), Nvidia ( NVDA), On Semiconductors ( ON ) and Qualcomm ( QCOM). Microsoft ( MSFT) was investing an additional $10B in OpenAI.

Sixteen Objects exhibition marks 70th anniversary of Israel's Yad Vashem Holocaust memorial. It brings back to Germany everyday objects that Jews took with them when they fled the Nazis. Lore Mayerfeld was 4 years old when she escaped from the Nazis in 1941. She found a safe haven in the United States and later immigrated to Israel. Her doll, Inge, was a present from her grandparents who were killed in the Holocaust.
Google is looking to expand the Fuchsia operating system from its current home on the Nest Hub to other smart devices and other form factors.

The iOS 16.3 update for older Apple devices is not available for iPhone 6, iPad mini 2 and iPad mini 3. The iOS 12.5.7 update contains a security update to fix a zero-day WebKit vulnerability that could allow a hacker to execute arbitrary code on Mac.

Angela Bassett got a supporting actress nomination for "Black Panther: Wakanda Forever". Gina Prince-Bythewood's "The Woman King" was snubbed from the Oscar nominations. Andrea Riseborough was nominated for her performance in the indie "To Leslie". Ana de Armas got a coveted nomination for the generally poorly received "Blonde". No Black woman has ever been nominated for best director.

Jamie Lee Curtis got a supporting actress Oscar nomination for "Everything Everywhere All at Once" on Tuesday morning. It was her first Oscar nomination after a long career in Hollywood. Her co-star Stephanie Hsu, Angela Bassett, Michelle Yeoh, Hong Chau and Kerry Condon were also nominated.
Kang Lee studies what happens physiologically to children when they lie. He explains why we should celebrate when kids start to lie and presents new lie-detection technology.

C/2022 E3 (ZTF) is a long-period comet that hasn't been near Earth for 50,000 years. It's arriving after a long journey from the Oort cloud. It will graze past the Earth close to the north celestial pole on February 1 this year.

Marina Horiuchi, Haruna Ishii, Miyu Kishi, Saki Kitazawa, Hana Taguchi, Reina Seiji, and Hideo Tsuchida are the main cast members for the stage play adaptation of the TV anime. It will run at the Shibuya Cultural Center Owada from May 17 to 21.

Dani Dyer is pregnant with twins with boyfriend Jarrod Bowen. She shared a photo of a bowl of pickles on Instagram on Tuesday. The reality star can't get enough of the food. On Sunday, she celebrated her son Santiago's 2nd birthday.

Elon Musk said Google had a "standing interest" in buying Tesla in testimony in the securities fraud trial. The billionaire pointed to the interest from Google's parent Alphabet as he defended his 2018 "funding secured" tweet in an ongoing civil trial. According to a 2015 book, Musk and former Google CEO Larry Page had an $11 billion deal in place for Tesla, but it fell through due to differences over specifics.

There are many women in extreme left armed groups. Far-left ideologies are based on emancipation and non-discrimination. Women make up a third of clandestine armed groups, more rife in extreme-left organisations than in the extreme right or in political-religious organisations.

Southern Hospitality's season 1 finale airs on Bravo on Monday night. It's been a great learning experience for stars Maddi Reese and Grace Lilly. Maddi and Trevor are still an item and are planning to move in together. Grace has found love with a mystery man.

Bang & Olufsen Beosound Theatre is a high-end, all-in-one Dolby Atmos soundbar. It costs from $6,890 to $7,990 depending on the finish. It has a variety of sound presets to choose from, including Spotify Connect, Apple TV, Music, Game.

Oxford University has a £4billion partnership with Legal & General. The Life and Mind Building will be the biggest construction project ever undertaken by the university and its largest teaching and research facility. L&G is one of the largest pension fund managers in the UK and has a growing business in America. The company's shares are £2.55 and should move higher as it profits from changes in the pensions market and chief executive Nigel Wilson pushes on with a robust growth plan.
Screen Time is Apple’s tool for restricting access to content, apps, and features on tablets. The latest iPadOS 16.3 update includes a security update for the feature.
Tips for getting your loved ones to help you with a move. Angi recommends following the following five tips.
California proposes a wealth tax on people with more than $50 million worth of assets. Stuart Varney says it's an attempt to get into the capital Americans built. He thinks it's a bad idea.
DevZero has raised $26 million in new funding. The company was founded by Debo Ray, a former Uber engineer. It has 21 employees and is hiring.

Rocket Lab is launching its first mission from Virginia today at 6 pm EST. The rocket will carry a trio of spacecraft to low Earth orbit for HawkEye 360, a Virginia-based company that collects and analyzes radio frequency analytics using its own satellite constellation. The launch is part of a three-mission contract HawkEye signed with Rocket Lab last April. Rocket Lab chose Virginia over NASA's Kennedy Space Center and the U.S. Space Force's Cape Canaveral in Florida because of the quietness of the range and increased launch cadence.

Apple introduced the Mac Studio in March 2022. In January 2023 Apple introduced a Mac mini with M2 Pro chip. The Mac mini is a good value for money. It costs $1,500 less than the M1 Max variant of the 16-inch MacBook Air.

Pamela Anderson has written a memoir called Love, Pamela. In it, she describes an uncomfortable encounter she had with Tim Allen on the set of Home Improvement in 1991. Allen denies the allegation. The memoir chronicles Anderson’s modest upbringing in Canada, her career posing for Playboy and starring in Baywatch, the series that made her an international star.

Guy Pearce has deleted two now-deleted tweets from the weekend that appeared to throw some shade in Cate Blanchett's direction. Guy has since clarified that he doesn't have any hard feelings towards Cate. Cate is up for an Oscar nomination for her role in the drama Tár.

Ford's factory in Saarlouis, Germany is scheduled to stop producing cars in 2025. Ford is talking to several parties about taking over the plant, including Chinese carmaker BYD. Ford has about 15 interested parties interested in buying the facility.

Sam Smith was kicked off Tinder and Hinge because the services didn't believe it was actually them. The Unholy artist appeared on Saturday Night Live over the weekend. The Stay With Me artist has been romantically linked to Christian Cowan, Jay Camilleri, Andy Newton Lee and Brandon Flynn.
Pilates is the ideal workout for getting lean and toned. Us Weekly recommends a range of products to help you get your workout on.

Ticketmaster's system crashed during the presale for Taylor Swift's upcoming "Eras" tour in November. Lawmakers are holding a Judiciary Committee hearing on the issue. Live Nation and Ticketmaster's 2010 merger has given the company an outsized influence on the market.
Ghislaine Maxwell has given a TalkTV interview from a Florida prison. She believes Jeffrey Epstein was murdered in prison and she doesn't remember the infamous photo with Prince Andrew ever existing.

Infinity Pool is a horror film starring Alexander Skarsgard and Mia Goth. It's about a couple enjoying an all-inclusive beach vacation in the fictional island of La Tolqa. The film is directed by Possessor's Brandon Cronenberg. It contains scenes of executions, orgies and full-frontal nudity.

The U.S. government is in a political standoff over raising the $31.4 trillion federal debt ceiling. A government shutdown could be worse than a government shutdown. A 2011 budget battle brought Washington to the brink of default.

Kylian Mbappé scored five goals in PSG's 7-0 win over Pays de Cassel in the French Cup match on Monday. He is the first player in club history to score that many goals in a match for PSG. It's the second time this season that he's scored a hat trick for PSg.

US Marines bamboozled the AI-based DARPA robot by pretending to be people. The robot's AI only focuses on humans walking. It doesn't account for people doing somersaults, hiding in cardboard boxes, and disguising themselves as trees.

Lockwood & Co is a new Netflix supernatural detective series based on Jonathan Stroud's book series. The series stars Ruby Stokes, Cameron Chapman, and Ali Hadji-Heshmati. It's one of Netflix's better supernatural series.
19% of all cars sold in California last year were zero-emission vehicles (ZEVs). About 346,000 ZEVs were sold in the state in 2022, with Tesla's Model 3 leading the sales charts.

Jemima Goldsmith met Jason Donovan at the premiere of her new film What's Love Got To Do With It? on Monday night. They haven't seen each other for about 30 years. Jemima also spoke about how living in Pakistan helped shape her into the person she is today.

Polestar has announced a comprehensive refresh for its Polestar 2 hatchback. It includes new motors, a slightly larger battery pack for some versions and a change in priorities. The rear-wheel-drive version now permits charging at a peak 205 kw, rather than 155 kw for those other models. The driving range of all-wheel drive versions has improved as well, now at up to 270 miles. The Performance Pack now includes Brembo brakes, 20-inch forged alloy wheels, dual-flow Öhlins dampers, and the Polestars Engineered software upgrade.

Ana de Armas got an Oscar nomination for her performance as Marilyn Monroe in Netflix's "Blonde" De Armas is the first Cuban actress to be nominated for a leading role at the Oscars. The movie has been criticized for its portrayal of trauma and suffering. It got eight Razzie Award nominations, including worst picture and screenplay.

The FBI conducted a thorough search of President Joe Biden's Delaware home on Friday. It was a "planned, consensual search" and an "unprecedented" top-to-bottom scouring of a sitting president's personal home. The documents with classified markings were found after previous batches of documents dating back to his time as vice president had been reported on at the president's Washington, D.C., office and Wilmington residence in recent weeks. The House Oversight Committee has been seeking various documents from the White House.
Watch the full interview with Liz Ann Sonders, Charles Schwab's chief investment strategist, on CNBC.

Siddharth Kara's new book, "Cobalt Red," is about the exploitation of cobalt, a mineral essential to batteries of smart devices and electric vehicles. Half of the world's cobalt reserves are found in the Democratic Republic of Congo. Human rights abuses and child labor are rife in Congo's mining sector.
FDA considering new COVID vaccine strategy for annual shots. Independent advisers are likely to weigh in on guidance that could simplify public health messaging.

The Supreme Court is hearing arguments on the legality of the no contact apprehension policy (NCAP). The policy uses CCTV and digital cameras to identify and apprehend traffic violators. LGU issues traffic citation tickets and mail them directly to the vehicle's registered owners. The transport groups argued that the NCAP is unconstitutional.
Boston Celtics are first in the Eastern Conference. Miami Heat are sixth in the league. The teams meet for the fourth time this season. The Heat won the last meeting 120-116 in overtime on Dec. 3.

Tyre Nichols died on January 10 after being stopped by Memphis police for reckless driving. Five officers were fired after an internal investigation into the incident. The family's attorneys are looking into possible criminal charges against the former officers.

Lamborghini has filed a patent for a hybrid V12 coupe with the World Intellectual Property Office in North Macedonia. CarBuzz found a sound clip of the V12 in pure electric mode filed with the European Intellectual Property office. The clip presents three modes of the electric driving sounds required of all electric-capable vehicles.

DeMar DeRozan scored 26 points, Zach LaVine 20 and Nikola Vucevic 14. Patrick Williams had a double-double of 18 points and 10 rebounds, while Alex Caruso (12 points), Coby White (10), and Clint Capela (16 points, 12 rebounds) also scored in double figures for Chicago. Trae Young scored 21 points and 13 assists for Atlanta. Billy Donovan coached his 200th game for the Bulls and 600th of his NBA coaching career.

Twitter is being sued by the landlord of its San Francisco headquarters for not paying $3.4 million in rent for January. The owner of the premises in central London is also taking the company to court over rental debt. Twitter has already been taken to court this month for falling behind on rent at another San Francisco office. Elon Musk bought Twitter for $44 billion last year and is cutting costs.

Twins acquire Michael A. Taylor from Royals for two prospects. Left-handed pitcher Evan Sisk and right-handed Steven Cruz go to Kansas City as part of the deal. To make room for Taylor on the 40-man roster, the Twins designated reliever A.J. Alexy for assignment.

The U.S. Border Patrol's BORTAC team from Uvalde, Texas, was called to end the siege at Robb Elementary School on May 24. The team's commander arrived on the scene at 12:09 p.m., 30 minutes before the shooting ended. The incident took place less than 80 miles from Mexico and involved 150 agents.
Ticketmaster learned lessons from the Taylor Swift concert tickets sale last year that was disrupted by record bot traffic. Live Nation Entertainment will tell a U.S. Senate committee on Tuesday.

A gunman killed 11 people at a ballroom dance studio in Monterey Park, California, during Lunar New Year celebrations. The suspect, Huu Can Tran, 72, died of a self-inflicted wound in a parking lot in Torrance, 25 miles south of the dance studio. Rev. Joseph Magdaong will celebrate a special Mass on Friday to pray for the victims and for the community. Mag daong was among the Christian and Jewish leaders who attended a candlelight vigil Monday night at Monterey park City Hall.

Bank of America, JPMorgan, and several other large banks will launch a digital wallet later this year. It will be compatible with Visa and Mastercard-branded cards. The banks have two main objectives: Tighten customer relationships and reduce online fraud.

Willie Nelson turns 90 years old on April 29th. He will be the guest of honor at two tribute concerts at the Hollywood Bowl in L.A. on that date. The lineup includes Bob Weir, the Chicks, Margo Price, Lukas Nelson, Billy Strings, Beck, Miranda Lambert, and Neil Young.
In Rockford, Illinois, three people died and two were injured in a shooting this month. 12 people were shot in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, over the weekend.

Spencer picked Vogue Williams up from the Global Radio studios on his Triumph Motorbike. Vogue recently tried to bar Spencer from her My Therapist Ghosted Me tour. She is opening her show with her comedian co-host Joanne McNally at the Gaiety Theatre in Dublin on February 16th.
Chess.com is struggling to cope with the growing popularity of the game online. The platform has issues with its servers and it's working to fix it.
Karen Khachanov will play Stefanos Tsitsipas or Jiri Lehecka in the Australian Open semifinals. Sebastian Korda had to quit the match in the third set because of a wrist injury.

The Oscar nominations for the 95th Academy Awards were announced on Tuesday. Tom Cruise was snubbed for Best Actor. There were no female directors nominated. Andrea Riseborough, Brian Tyree Henry and Stephanie Hsu were among the unexpected actors to be nominated.

Josh Allen had to change his throwing motion because of the elbow injury he suffered in the team's Week 9 loss to the New York Jets. He didn't miss a single game because of it, but he was listed on the injury report with it through the end of the season. Allen completed 62.5% of his passes for 1,880 yards and 16 touchdowns with six interceptions.

There was a mass shooting in Half Moon Bay on Monday afternoon. It was the third mass killing in California in eight days. Governor Gavin Newsom was visiting victims of the Monterey Park shooting when he was told about the Halfmoon Bay incident. Newsom called for the banning of high capacity magazines.
Catastrophic storms devastated California's economy and left more than $1 billion in damages. Global warming has made weather events more expensive.

Ticketmaster is the world's largest ticket seller, processing 500 million tickets each year in more than 30 countries. 70% of tickets for major concert venues in the U.S. are sold through Ticketmaster. Last year, the company's website crashed during a Taylor Swift presale.

Six Nations Chief Executive Ben Morel says there are no plans to expand the championship or change the participants. There are reports of interest from South Africa's rugby union in joining the Six Nations. South Africa have been aligning themselves with the northern hemisphere.
Tyre Nichols' family was shown the police body cam footage of the Jan. 7 traffic stop that preceded his death.

Guy Pearce posted a series of 'shady' tweets about Cate Blanchett after she won Best Actress for her performance in Tár at the Critics' Choice Awards. He deleted all of the tweets on Monday. Twitter sleuths dug into Pearce's past to find out why he had a problem with Blanchetto. He was offered a role in Poor Boy at Melbourne Theatre Company's production of the play, but refused to take it because she didn't pay him the same salary.

BlockFi filed for chapter 11 bankruptcy in late November following the collapse of FTX. The company has $160 million in loans backed by 68,000 Bitcoin mining rigs which it needs to sell. Almost $4 billion was raised through these loans since the last crypto bull run. Grayscale set up a fund with Foundry to invest in BTC mining hardware.

The average 30-year mortgage interest rate dropped to 6.15% last week, the lowest in 18 weeks. The Federal Reserve has been steadily increasing the benchmark Federal Funds rate. The recent dip in rates represents a significant savings for homebuyers. The mortgage interest rates are currently 0.93% lower than they were last fall. For a $500,000 home loan, a 0.3% lower rate saves you $300+ on monthly payment and over $110,000 in interest over the life of the loan.
Ludlow scored the game's first six goals in a 12-3 win over Southwick.
We may earn a commission from links on this page.

Amazon.com has signed an unsecured $8 billion term loan at the benchmark Secure Overnight Financing Rate plus 0.75% with an additional 0.1% credit spread adjustment. The loan is earmarked for general corporate purposes and matures in 364 days. TD Securities was the sole lead arranger, with ANZ, BBVA, Bank of China, Credit Agricole, DBS, Mizuho and NatWest as joint bookrunners.

Tulare County Board of Supervisors this week denied an appeal from Sundale Vineyards. Tulare City Council is expected to approve the sale of nearly 60 acres to the new company. Fresno Mayor Ashley Swearengin will hold a live town hall television broadcast January 5.

Executives at Target and Walmart are raising alarms about shoplifting in their stores. Organized crime is selling stolen goods on online marketplaces like Amazon, Craigslist, eBay and Facebook Marketplace. The number of shoplifts increased 60% between 2015 and 2020.

Josiah Vargas was picking up his breakfast order at McDonald's drive-thru when he realized that the employee at the window had given him more than he ordered. He returned the money to the McDonald's with a bag full of cash.
All Songs Considered's New Mix features boygenius, The National, Baaba Maal, Miss Gritt, Niklas Paschburg, The Hackles and Miss Grit.

Chris Stapleton will sing the national anthem at Super Bowl LVII on February 12 in Glendale, Arizona. Mickey Guyton, Eric Church, Jazmine Sullivan, Faith Hill, the Chicks, Carrie Underwood, and Luke Bryan have all done it before. Stapletons was named the 2022 CMA Male Vocalist of the Year back in November.

The Podcast Academy has tapped Larry Wilmore to host its third annual Awards for Excellence in Audio. The March 7 ceremony will be livestreamed on Twitch from the International Theater in Las Vegas from 6-7:30 p.m. PT. The 2023 Ambies will highlight 185 nominees across 26 categories with winners to be selected by voting members.

Ticketmaster is the world's largest ticket seller, processing 500 million tickets each year in more than 30 countries. Last year, the company's website crashed during a Taylor Swift presale. Sen. Amy Klobuchar, a Minnesota Democrat, said Ticketmaster's market dominance means it faces little pressure to innovate and improve.
KAUST-led investigation shows how the fastening enzyme involved in DNA repair seals DNA nicks. The research is published in Nature Communications.

No 1 Grosvenor Square was designed by Eric Parry Architects. It was the US Embassy between 1938 and 1960 and the Canadian High Commission until 2014. It is now an exclusive apartment block with luxury apartments. Prices start at £8.65m.

The official website for the television anime of Norio Sakurai's The Dangers in My Heart manga revealed four new cast members for the anime on Tuesday. Nobuhiko Okamoto, Gen Sato, Aki Toyosaki and Jun Fukushima are the new actors. The anime will premiere on and its affiliates in the "NUMAnimation" programming block in April. Seven Seas Entertainment licensed the manga.
Google Home Hub can translate 26 different languages. The interpreter mode of the Google Home Hub is better than Google Translate. You can't use interpreter mode while on a call.

Lenovo is offering their 11-inch ThinkPad Yoga 11e Gen 5 2-in-1 laptop for only $249 as part of a winter sale. It's $750 off the usual price of $999. The laptop has an Intel Celeron processor, 8 GB of memory, and a 128 GB of storage.

Mikaela Shiffrin won her 83rd World Cup race on Tuesday. She broke a tie on the all-time women's list with Lindsey Vonn. Shiffrina needs three more wins to match Ingemar Stenmark's overall record of 86 victories.
Adam Klotz was attacked by a group of teenagers on a New York City subway car over the weekend. He tried to stop them from harassing an elderly man.

James Norton's odds have been cut to take over Daniel Craig's role as James Bond after Sunday's episode of Happy Valley. Viewers were impressed by the shirtless prison scenes, a dramatic fight and Tommy Lee Royce's escape from Leeds court.
U.K. public borrowing in December was the highest for the last month of the year in at least 29 years. Public sector borrowing reached £27.4 billion ($33.7 billion) in December.

Conor McGregor's spokesperson denies the woman's accusations that he kicked and punched her on his yacht in Ibiza last year. The incident happened after a night of partying to celebrate McGregor's birthday in July 2022.

Max-Planck-Institut für Kohlenforschung has developed a new method of controlling the selectivity of chemical reactions using a special catalyst and the energy of light. The method could be useful in the field of synthesis.

Novak Djokovic has been accused of faking his injury at the Australian Open. He won his 25th match at the Grand Slam on Monday despite a hamstring injury. He was deported on the eve of the last year's tournament in Melbourne. Victoria Azarenka was questioned over her 10-minute timeout for a rib injury in the 2013 Australian Open semifinal match.

LeBron James will become the NBA’s all-time scoring champion in the next fortnight. He has won four NBA titles and reached ten NBA Finals in his 20-year NBA career. He is known for diving head first into whatever endeavor piques his interest. James has always spoken his mind about off-court endeavors.
Peter Jackson, an addiction psychiatrist at the University of Vermont Medical Center, suggests shifting focus for the remainder of month.

"Everything Everywhere All at Once" and "The Fabelmans" are up for best picture at the 95th Academy Awards. "The Banshees of Inisherin" is also up for the best picture. "Top Gun: Maverick" got seven nominations.

Street Fighter 6 is coming out on June 2, 2023 for PC, PS4, PS5, and Xbox Series X|S. It's the sixth mainline entry in the Street Fighter franchise. The full launch roster for Street Fighter 6 has been revealed.

There are many places to put Google Home or Nest smart speakers and displays in your home. Dale Smith has six Google Home speakers and two Nest Hubs displays in his two-bedroom townhouse. Colin McDonald has a Google Home in his home office.
Writer Sakeina Syed is critical of HBO's new show Velma and the trend of appearance-based jokes about brown girls on TV. Syed grew up as a young brown girl in the early 2000s.

The plan also includes provisions to "Supplement African-American income of lower income households to reflect the Area Median Income (AMI) annually for 250 years,” “Finance a comprehensive debt forgiveness program,’ and “Convert public housing units into condominiums with a $1 buy-in for qualifying residents. The committee did not include an estimated total cost if the plan were to go into effect. To date, San Francisco has roughly 45,000 black residents. The company has trouble retaining workers after applying for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. 11 workers quit their positions between the day the petition was submitted on Nov. 28 and the declaration was filed on Jan. 23.

Jan Valtin's 1941 autobiography, Out of the Night, sold a million copies in the United States. It was a Book-of-the-Month-Club selection, Life and Reader’s Digest each ran excerpts, and it was a stand-in for a broader political conflict playing out in America. It became a tool to dodge or to sling at your enemy, and then it was forgotten.

Miranda Lambert and Jelly Roll have been writing songs together lately. Lambert is the reigning ACM entertainer of the year. Jelly Roll recently earned his first Country Airplay No. 1 with “Son of a Sinner” and has played the Grand Ole Opry stage with Craig Morgan and Brantley Gilbert.

The HERA team reports that it has doubled the sensitivity of the array of 350 radio telescopes in the Karoo desert of South Africa. HERA has yet to detect radio emissions from the end of the cosmic dark ages, but its results provide clues to the composition of stars and galaxies in the early universe. The data suggest that early galaxies contained very few elements besides hydrogen and helium, unlike our galaxies today.
The Razzies nominated Blonde as one of the worst movies of the year. Ana de Armas got a Best Actress Oscar nomination for her performance as Marilyn Monroe in the movie.

Justin Moore was laid off by Google at 3:00 a.m. on Friday. He started out as a senior software engineer at the company in 2006 and progressed to the position of software-engineering manager in 2019. He was one of 12,000 people affected by Google's mass layoffs last week.

Andrea Thompson, Tristan Thompson's mother, died of a heart attack in Toronto on January 6. Khloé is mourning the loss of Andrea. The reality TV star took to Instagram to express her grief. She wrote about her relationship with Andrea and their children Amari.

In 2022, the average tax refund was a hearty $3,039. The IRS warned that the average refund may be lower than last year. The main thing is to think about where you want your money to go and not to spend it all at once. Start an emergency fund, pay off debt, save for an upcoming expense, or make home improvements.

General Colonel Mikhail Teplinsky was one of Moscow's key operational commanders in Ukraine. He was dismissed as a result of a power struggle among the Russian top brass, according to British intelligence.

Aleksandar Vucic warns Serbia against rejecting a new Western plan for normalizing relations with Kosovo. The plan stipulates that Serbia would not be against membership of Kosovo in international organizations, including the UN. Serbia and Kosovo have been at odds since the 1998-99 war, which ended with NATO intervention.

Two high school students were killed and one injured in a gang-related shooting in Des Moines. An 18-year-old has been arrested and charged with two counts of murder in the first degree, attempted murder and criminal gang participation.

Canada is getting hotter and our weather is getting weirder due to climate change. The Arctic is warming faster than anywhere else on the planet. California is exporting its own precious water to feed others.

Ian Williams will chair the 2023 Scotiabank Giller Prize jury. The $100,000 prize is the biggest in Canadian literature. Joining Williams on the jury are Canadian writers Sharon Bala and Brian Thomas Isaac, American author Rebecca Makkai and Indian writer Neel Mukherjee.

Boris Johnson is in hot water over claims he used a distant cousin called Sam Blyth as a guarantor for an £800,000 loan. Richard Sharp is accused of helping to facilitate that loan - just as he was successfully applying to be BBC chairman. Sharp is a former banker who used to be Rishi Sunak’s boss at Goldman Sachs. Sunak is facing another mess involving the chairman of the Tory Party, Nadhim Zahawi. Zahawi ended up paying HMRC around £5 million while he was chancellor following a dispute over his tax liabilities.

Benjamin Shamgar hosted one of Nelly's afterparties at Flamingo Lounge in Potts Point on January 14. Nelly performed at Juicy Fest in Melbourne last Wednesday. The Dilemma rapper has since been criticised for his on-stage behaviour.
Karine Jean-Pierre accused House Republicans of wanting to raise gas prices. She was widely criticized on social media for putting the blame on Republicans instead of the Obama administration.

Twitter is being sued over unpaid rent payments in its London and San Francisco offices. The landlord of the San Francisco office claims Twitter breached the contract by not raising its line of credit by $10 million.

At least seven people were killed in two shootings in the Northern California beach city of Half Moon Bay. The suspect, Zhao Chunli, 67, was arrested two hours after the shootings while sitting in a parked car at a sheriff’s substation. On Lunar New Year's Eve, a man opened fire at the Star Ballroom Dance Studio in Monterey Park, killing 10 people at the scene and wounding 10 others. Brandon Tsay, 26, who owns the Alhambra dance studio, wrestled the gun from the gunman and stopped him from entering the building.

Woot is offering a one-day sale on refurbished Apple products. Preowned devices from Apple are on sale. Previous-gen iPhone 13 is included in the sale. The iPhone 12 is $219 less than buying new from Apple directly. The sale expires tonight at 9:59 p.m. PT (12:59 a.m., ET)

Ralphie is a 26-pound black-and-white dog up for adoption at Niagara SPCA in Niagara Falls, New York. The shelter's Facebook post has gone viral. Ralphie's first owners took him to board and train, but their relationship was built on the premise that Ralphie was the boss, so things ended abruptly.
Two families want to take care for a child, known as "Baby L" to protect her identity. Marine is accused of kidnapping the child from Afghan couple.

It's been seven years since the B-word infected every political discussion in the UK. Both sides considered themselves to be saving the British people from catastrophic harm by leaving the EU. Now, the government's economists say it's costing the economy £100bn a year. The Nuffield Trust has just published a study showing that Brexit is damaging the NHS.

Priscilla Gartenmayer posted a video on TikTok showing her family finding her cousin, Dylan Garten mayer, who'd been missing for three hours. Dylan had been free diving on Jan. 19 and got caught in the Gulf Stream current. He had to swim more than a mile to reach a channel marker. He was rescued by the Coast Guard.

Lisa McClain is a member of the House Committee on Oversight and Accountability. She is concerned about the discovery of classified documents in the garage of President Biden's son, Hunter, six days before the midterms. The committee will investigate the matter.

A new simulation of stellar dynamics explains why star cores don't spin as fast as they should. The study was conducted by Florence Marcotte, Ludovic Petitdemange and Christophe Gissinger of École Normale Supérieure in France. It suggests that magnetic fields in the radiative regions of stars create a self-sustaining loop that slows the star core's spin.

Dead Island 2 is a follow-up to the original Dead Island game. It was announced in 2014, but has been delayed twice. It will be released on April 28, 2023. The game will be available on PS5, Xbox Series X|S, PS4, Xbox One, and PC.

Matt Tome was promoted to Vice President at Heritage Group. Kevin Ryan, Vice President, and Franklin Garstin, Associate, were added to the investment team. Heritage has over $700 million of assets under management and seeks to make investments in high-growth healthcare services and healthcare technology businesses.
Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg joins "Power Lunch" to discuss the distribution of funds from the 1.2 trillion dollar transportation bill.

"Everything Everywhere All at Once" and "The Banshees of Inisherin" are the most nominated films for the 95th Academy Awards. The best picture race contains the two highest-grossing films of the year, "Avatar: The Way of Water" and  "Top Gun: Maverick" and the musical biopic "Elvis". The last two best director winners, Jane Campion and Chloe Zhao, were women. Ke Huy Quan, a former child actor, earned a best supporting actor nomination for his work in "Everything Everywhere"
Hair transplants can be done in Turkey for a fraction of the cost in the U.S. and the recovery takes 6 to 8 months. The results of the procedure are not known for a year.

Natasha Lyonne plays Charlie in the new mystery series "Poker Face" and she likes it. Lyonne's character is partly inspired by Jeff Bridges' character in "The Big Lebowski" and partly by her personality. The series follows a procedural format with each episode showing the murder, then flashback and seeing where Charlie was during the murder. There are many guest stars in the series, including Lil Rey Henry, Tim Meadows, Luis Guzman, Chloë Sevigny and Nick Nolte.
No. 5 St. Joseph (Mont.) and No. 19 Donovan Catholic will play a football game at MetLife Stadium on Friday, September 30, 2022.

Department of Energy is expanding partnerships with battery manufacturers to help them redesign and reduce the costs of future batteries. The companies include Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. and Panasonic Corp. There is a growing demand for better batteries.

The new MacBook pro is a beautifully crafted gadget that has a balanced, thoughtful feel. It's a high-resolution panel and very bright LCD screen with miniLED backlights. The keyboard is what Apple calls the magic keyboard. The battery life is up to 22 hours on the 16in MacBook pro with no drop.

Disney closed Splash Mountain at Disney World's Magic Kingdom on Sunday. It was the last day to ride the ride, which opened in 1989. The theme of the ride is changing from Song of the South to Princess & the Frog, which is based on Disney's first Black princess Tiana. The new version of the new ride is scheduled to open in 2024.
Esther Crawford was reprimanded for arranging a one-to-one meeting with Elon Musk in Twitter's cafe before the deal closed. She went viral for sleeping on the office floor days after Musk's takeover.

Tory MPs believe Nadhim Zahawi will no longer be Tory chairman in 24 hours' time. He is under increasing pressure after it emerged he paid HMRC around £5 million over an unpaid tax bill when he was chancellor last year.

Rashaun Woods has been a part of Oklahoma's football scene for the better part of three decades. He starred at Millwood High School and Oklahoma State, then after a short professional career came back, started coaching and became the head coach at John Marshall and Enid. He also spent time commentating on football on local radio.
Sabrina Carpenter delivered new songs for Ariana Grande. Nonsense feels adult and honest.
Tyre Nichols' family met with Memphis officials and saw the body camera footage from his arrest.
ChatGPT, an online chatbot powered by artificial intelligence, has been used to create disinformation and propaganda. The company that created ChatGPT is studying the issue.

TikTok is enforcing attendance requirements for remote workers. Disney, Apple, Snap, and Twitter have recently enacted similar policies. TikTok's monthly active user count in the U.S. fell to 110 million from 113 million in January.

Zach Shallcross sent home contestant Madison Johnson before the first rose ceremony on Monday's season 27 premiere of The Bachelor on ABC. Madison, 26, a business owner from Fargo, North Dakota, cried after seeing Zach hit it off with other women. Brianna Thorbourne, 24, from Jersey City, received the first impression rose.

Professor is teaching a history class on history as told through the medium of video games. Each week, he will talk about a game that he played and talk about how it portrays history. This week he talks about Bury Me, My Love.

Mark Cuban is trying to create an online prescription filling service called Cost Plus Drugs. It's a competitor to Amazon Pharmacy, which charges $5 for the fulfillment of three generic prescriptions each month. Cost Plus has a firm separation from insurance companies.

At the halfway point of the current season, we've reached the halfway of the Premier League. Manchester City is the leader, Liverpool is second, Chelsea is third, Arsenal and Tottenham are tied on 35 points, and Manchester United is one point back on 34. West Ham United is the team most likely to improve in the second half of the season.

Chess.com has 10 million active members, the most it's ever had. The site's servers are struggling to cope with the growing traffic. The problem is a technical bottleneck involving "unscalable" parts of the chess-playing platform. The website is adding more server hardware to address the problem.

Benjamin Netanyahu and King Abdullah II met for the first time in over four years on Tuesday. They discussed the status of a contested holy site in the Old City of Jerusalem sacred to both Jews and Muslims. Jordan's royal court said the king urged Israel to respect the status quo at the sacred compound, which Muslims call Noble Sanctuary and Jews call Temple Mount.

Spotify is cutting 6% of its staff as it struggles to cope with rising expenses and falling revenues. The company's CEO Daniel Ek commented that Spotify's operating expenses outpaced its revenue growth by two times in 2022. Spotify's Premium plan costs $9.99 per month. Apple Music and Amazon Music Unlimited are more expensive.

The victim, in his 60s, was found unresponsive and without his mobility scooter in the car park of a Tesco superstore in Stroud, Gloucestershire, at 6am on Sunday. He was taken to hospital, but died later that day. A mobility scoot was found abandoned almost two miles away in Bisley Old Road at 8am. A 40-year-old woman was arrested on suspicion of robbery and murder. Magistrates today granted police more time to question her.

Princess Eugenie is pregnant with her second child with husband Jack Brooksbank. They are already parents to their son August, 23 months. Eugenies and Beatrice are two of Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip’s eight grandkids.

Myleene Klass thinks it's tragic that the statutory menopause leave bill has not been passed through government. The TV presenter and host, 44, appeared on Jeremy Vine to debate the topic of women getting a menopausal leave with their employers. She also compares the health woes women experience between the ages of 45-55 to people going through health issues and getting sick leave. Andrew Pierce claims the government is against it because it will discriminate against men.

Tom Brady and Gisele Bündchen are going through a difficult time in their marriage. Chris Simms, an NFL analyst, thinks Brady might quit the game midseason. Simms thinks he's more likely to quit than Aaron Rodgers.

Lisa Marie Presley died on Jan. 12 at the age of 54 at West Hills Hospital in Los Angeles. She was laid to rest at Graceland with her father, Elvis, and her son, Benjamin Keough. Priscilla thanks her fans for their condolences. The cause of death has not been determined.

Meri Brown has starred on the TLC reality series since its premiere in 2010. Before the show, Meri worked in the mental health field and aspired to work with at-risk youths. She runs Lizzie’s Heritage Inn, a bed-and-breakfast in Southern Utah. Meri and Kody broke up after nearly 33 years of marriage. She is worth an estimated $400,000.

Jonathan Isaac returned to the Orlando Magic on Monday night after a 2½-year absence. He scored 10 points on 4-of-7 shooting in 10 minutes of action as the Magic defeated the Boston Celtics 113-98. Isaac's last game at the Amway Center was on Dec. 30, 2019, when he contributed 13 points, 9 rebounds, 2 assists, 3 steals and 2 blocks in a loss to Atlanta Hawks.

The Crown Estate launched court proceedings against Twitter over unpaid rent at the company's office space in central London's West End neighborhood. The estate manages the British monarchy's vast property portfolio worth $19.2 billion. It generated $385 million in revenue last year. Twitter has been rocked by turmoil since Elon Musk purchased the company in a $44 billion takeover.
Meta announced new features for Messenger, including default end-to-end encrypted chats, Active Status, group profile photos, chat themes, custom emojis and reactions and a few more.
Republicans are running an ad against Sen. Joe Manchin after he spent a week in Davos and it was revealed he has racked up a $1million fine dining bill.

Beyonce has been slammed for her $24m Dubai concert. She didn't perform any songs from her new album, which was dedicated to her late gay uncle Jonny. Her father Matthew, 71, has defended the concert, saying it united a diverse crowd. He also revealed that Beyonce is planning a tour where she will perform songs from Renaissance.

Dolly Parton's first rock 'n' roll album - Rock Star - is rumored to drop this autumn. It will feature Stevie Nicks, Annie Lennox, Joan Jett, Steve Perry, Steven Tyler, and John Fogerty. She sang with Elton John on one of his songs for her album. Miley Cyrus will take part in Rock Star. She hasn't secured Cher yet, but she hopes to do a duet with her soon.

"Flowers" by Miley Cyrus is the new No. 1 on the Billboard Hot 100 songs chart. Bizarrap and Shakira's "Bzrp Music Sessions, Vol. 53" debuts at No. 9. The Hot 100 blends all-genre U.S. streaming, radio airplay, and sales data.

Elvis Presley and Priscilla Beaulieu spent their honeymoon at the Palm Springs estate where they stayed. The 4-bedroom, 5-bathroom, 4,695-square-foot home was designed by renowned architect William Krisel and originally served as Robert Alexander's personal residence. Elvis and his new wife stayed there for a year after their wedding. The house was called "The House of Tomorrow" by Look magazine in 1962.

Amy Robach and T.J. Holmes got caught having an affair and were fired from GMA. Now it's been revealed that T. J. had at least two other affairs while working at ABC. One of them was with married producer Natasha Singh. The other one was with Jasmin Pettaway, 24, who was working as an intern at ABC in 2015. Amy is shocked by all the news and doesn't know how she's being treated by the network.

Sean Penn and Robin Wright were spotted together at LAX and in Los Angeles this week. They were married from 1996 to 2010. They have two children together: son Hopper Penn, 29, and daughter Dylan Penn, 31.
Rodgers could be traded this offseason if the price is right. He is due around $60 million for 2023. The Packers have Jordan Love as a replacement for Rodgers.
Episode 2 of HBO's The Last of Us aired on Sunday. Some fans are upset with the ending of the episode. The writers changed the ending from the original PlayStation 3 game.
Gary Payton believes the NBA is planning to put a team back in Seattle around 2025. The league used to have a team in Seattle, but it relocated to Oklahoma City after the 2007-08 season.

Connecticut Gov. Ned Lamont announced a series of proposed gun laws to curb rising gun violence. The proposals include a ban on open carrying of firearms, limiting handgun purchases to one per month, and spending $2.5 million on community anti-violence programs. Republicans criticize the proposals as focusing too much on law-abiding citizens and not enough on criminals.

Moscow residents are getting phone calls from unknown people claiming to be police officers warning them not to let their children out after 7 p.m. because convicts from Wagner's private army are returning from the battlefield and could be dangerous. Some of the convicts were serving time for pedophilia-related charges when they were set free by the private army. Yevgeny Prigozhin, the Kremlin-linked businessman behind Wagner, has previously claimed military officials and others in the Russian establishment were concocting smear campaigns against him.

Berchtold's remarks were more conciliatory and apologetic than past remarks from Live Nation executives. Live Nation Entertainment Chairman Greg Maffei said Swift's popularity was partly to blame. He apologized "to all our fans," but not to Swift directly. Ticketmaster sold 2 million tickets that day. The debacle spawned criticism from Swifties and elected officials alike.
Valentine's Day is one of the biggest jewelry gifting holidays. The best Valentine's Day gifts for women are from Blue Nile, GLDN and Mejuri.

Microwaves are a staple item that can make a big difference in the kitchen. Nikki Jones, Best Buy’s Home Expert, recommends choosing the right microwave for your lifestyle. She recommends looking for the right size for your kitchen and the capacity that fits the needs of your home. Microwaves with added features, like convection and speed cooking, can also be a great option for people who want to splurge.

Elon Musk is on the stand for a third day in a trial in federal court in San Francisco. He is being sued by Tesla investors who allege he misled them with a tweet. The 51-year-old billionaire is defending himself on two 2018 tweets.

The search for missing British actor Julian Sands has entered its 11th day. The search is taking place amid high winds and gusts of up to 67mph. Last week, Sands' family released the last known images of him mountaineering.

Dr. Oren Tepper, a plastic surgeon in New York, says it's common for weight loss to deflate key areas of the face, leading to a more aged appearance. Dr. Frank coined the term “Ozempic face” to describe the condition. Dermatologist Dhaval Bhanusali uses Radiesse in combination with Sculptra to restore volume.

Brandon Tsay disarmed the alleged Monterey Park shooter after he had allegedly killed 11 people and wounded nine others at a nearby location on Sunday. It was reminiscent of the deadly Club Q shooting in Colorado Springs, Colorado, in November, when two patrons tackled the shooter to the ground and held him down until police arrived. Psychiatrists say part of this is due to the fight-or-flight response, which is a psychological reaction that occurs in response to an event stressful, frightening or life-threatening.

Spotlight Search is available on all iPhones, iPads, and Macs that have an iOS 8 update or later. It can be accessed by swiping down from the middle of your home screen. It gives you all the options you need on one page.
Inflation and high inventory have created the perfect environment for sneaker collectors. The market for Nike and Yeezy has shrunk. Most shoes are easier to get now.

The Samsung Galaxy A13 5G is a reliable device with good performance, healthy battery life, and a decent camera. It's certified to use AT&T's newly enabled C-band spectrum, which promises faster-than-4G speeds and good signal reach. The MediaTek 700 5G chipset and its 4GB of RAM are strong points of the phone. The A13's replacement, the Galaxy A14 5G, will be released in January 2023 and will cost $199.

Martin Griffiths, the U.N. humanitarian chief and leaders of Save The Children and Care International are in Afghanistan. They are in the country to reverse the Taliban's crackdown on women and girls. The ban on Afghan women working for humanitarian organizations has put some aid programs on hold.

Ruben Gallego is running for Senate in Arizona against Kyrsten Sinema, who left the Democratic Party last month to run as an independent. Gallega is running to become the first Hispanic senator from Arizona.

The tech sector announced 31,000 job cuts in the first 20 days of January, including 10,000 at Microsoft and 12,000 from Alphabet. The media sector announced 3,774 job cuts from 2022 to 2021. Media layoffs are down 5% year-over-year, but up 20% from 2021.
Finland and Sweden are ready to join the NATO alliance, the State Department says. Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan said Sweden should not expect Turkey's support for its membership.

Apple's AR/VR headset is going to cost $3,000. It will have an interface that resembles iOS and will display immersive video with instant switching between AR and VR modes. The headset will have a Home Screen with familiar app icons, customisable display widgets and the option to use a keyboard and mouse as well as eye and hand tracking. It is rumoured to focus on videoconferencing and FaceTime-based video chats.
The Griffin Knight learned skill doesn't extend the movement of units if they move through the Griffin Knight's space.

Mike Pompeo will decide in the next few months if he wants to run for the White House in 2024. Pompeo is out with a new book, "Never Give an Inch: Fighting for the America I Love." Pompeo served as CIA director and secretary of state in the Trump administration.
Brendon Urie announced on Instagram that Panic! At The Disco has split up. The band's final tour begins in Vienna next month and ends on March 10 in Manchester, England.

Howard University has been awarded a five-year, $90 million contract to lead a research center focused on technology for military systems. It's the first such center at a historically Black college or university. Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin is determined to change the funding for research at HBCUs.

President Biden donated his Senate papers to the University of Delaware. The university has more than 1,800 boxes of his papers from his time in the Senate. Cruz wants the FBI to go through all the boxes and find out how many classified documents are in them.

Spotify is laying off about 6% of its employees. CEO Daniel Ek wrote a memo about the changes in the C-suite reorganization. He wrote that the changes will allow him to focus on Spotify's future. Leadership experts say the memo is tone-deaf and unsympathetic.

Money In The Bank will take place at The O2 in London on July 1, 2023. It will be the first WWE Premium Live Event to be held in London in over two decades. It follows the success of Cardiff’s Clash At The Castle in September 2022, the first major WWE stadium show in the UK since 1992.

Honor Beauvais, 12, died in a snowstorm on the Rosebud Sioux Reservation in South Dakota. Six people died in the winter storms that hit the reservation. The tribe is asking for a presidential disaster declaration.
A young dolphin wandered into a creek in Clearwater, Florida, and biologists had to form a human chain to pull it out. The animal was in good condition and was displaying normal behavior.

House Republicans will introduce a bill on Tuesday that would expand 529 education savings plans. The CHOICE Act would allow families with incomes up to 130% of the poverty level to use education funds deposited into a 529 savings account for grades K-12 at any institution. The bill would also allow parents to choose private or homeschooled children.

The New York Yankees signed Aaron Judge to a $360m contract through to the 2031 season. The slugger was a free agent this offseason and was pursued by the Giants and the San Diego Padres. Anthony Rizzo convinced him to stay with the Yankees.

Kyle Sandilands and Harry Connick Jr had a blow up over the phone. The radio shock jock, 51, and the American singer, 55, no longer speak off-set. The rivalry came to a head when Sandiland accused Connick of 'going on about the pronouns' of the contestants.
Smash these buttons for the weekend.

Jason Momoa and Emilia Clarke got together for a Game of Thrones reunion on Saturday night. They were celebrating the birthday of the series co-creator David Benioff. Clarke played the Mother of Dragons for all eight seasons of the HBO show. The duo were last seen together in October 2019.

Tanzanian cargo ship Anil has sunk in a jetty in the southern Iranian port of Assaluyeh. Rescue teams transferred the ship's crew to safety. The port is the main hub for shipment of gas and petrochemicals produced in Iran.

Viktor Vekselberg's superyacht Tango was seized by the U.S. government in April. Two men who managed the yacht were arrested in Spain on Friday. They allegedly tried to hide the yacht's ownership by using shell companies, intermediaries and bank accounts.
This Is Us actress, 38, recently gave birth to her second child, Ozzie. She also has a 23-month-old son, Gus, with her husband Taylor Goldsmith.

Ferdinand Romualdez Marcos, Jr. and other stakeholders oppose the implementation of TOP-CRMS/ECSSSF. They believe it will cause inflation and increase the cost of importing goods. They also oppose the transfer of empty containers to a 10-hectare facility outside the ports.

Killings of journalists around the world jumped by 50% in 2022 compared to the previous year. At least 67 news media workers were killed worldwide in 2022, the highest number since 2018. More than half of the 67 killings took place in Ukraine, Mexico and Haiti.

Elon Musk took the stand Monday for the first day of testimony in the federal shareholder trial over his 2018 declaration he had "Funding secured" to take Tesla private. He is testifying in U.S. District Court as a defendant in a class-action securities fraud lawsuit.
Wells Fargo initiated coverage of Chipotle as overweight. Zachary Fadem has a price target of $1,800 for the stock. The Mexican food chain has "best-in-class unit economics with an upside"
LAPD officials deliver an update on their investigation of the Monterey Park mass shooting.
The NJ.com Top 20 occupants had an orderly, upset free week two weeks ago.
Ron DeSantis disapproved of an African-American history course during a press conference on Monday (23 January). He was promoting Florida as 'the education state'.
Eric Mandl, Guggenheim Securities Senior Managing Director joins TechCheck to discuss tech M&A and the future of software.

Brandon Tsay, 26, saved lives when he wrestled a gun away from the suspect. Huu Can Tran, 72, is accused of shooting and killing 11 people and wounding others in Monterey Park, California. The massacre was the nation's fifth mass killing this month. One of the victims has been identified as 65-year-old Mymy Nhan.

Conor McGregor is denying all the accusations made by a guest on his boat. The woman accused him of assaulting her in Ibiza last summer. She told Irish police that she had to flee his yacht because she "feared for her life". She claims that McGregor suddenly became aggressive towards her and attacked her when she tried to get a mutual friend to help her.
Lawmakers are paying more attention to UFO sightings. Harvard physicist Avi Loeb believes scientists should take the lead in investigating cases.

Yoshio James Yoda, a Japanese actor and businessman, has died at the age of 88. He was an actor who appeared on all 138 episodes of McHale's Navy, a '60s TV series set in a fictionalized Pacific island base during World War II. Yoda played Fuji Kobiaji, the Japanese prisoner of war on the U.S. naval crew.
Audioscope is an audio visualizer that turns sine waves into circles. It's a mathematically simple way of working with signals.

The source code for League of Legends, Teamfight Tactics and a legacy anticheat platform were stolen in a "social engineering attack" that occurred last week. The thieves have sent Riot an email demanding an unspecified ransom. Riot will not pay. Riot warned that the exposure of the source code could lead to an uptick in new cheats. A hotfix for the 13.2 patch will roll out on January 26, but some material has been pushed to the 13 3 patch slated for February 8.
Madison Johnson is sent home before the rose ceremony on the season premiere of 'The Bachelor' on ABC.

Biden administration has yet to issue the rules that could expand asylum eligibility for migrants fleeing gang or domestic violence. The delay is due to internal debates within the administration. The administration is focusing on reducing unlawful border crossings.

Boat noodle soup is one of the essential dishes of Los Angeles. It's served at Sapp Coffee Shop and Mariscos Jalisco. Julia Gold was born in East L.A. and grew up eating there with Jonathan Gold. She was the food editor of Gourmet magazine. She's now the general manager of Times Food.

John Carney's "Flora and Son" has sold to Apple Original Films for $20 million. The film was premiered at the Sundance Film Festival this weekend. It's about a single mom (Eve Hewson) who finds a way to connect with her troubled teenage son (Oren Kinlan) through a shared love of music. Joseph Gordon-Levitt plays Flora's guitar teacher. Jack Reynor plays Floras' self-absorbed ex-husband.
A majority of Britons think Nadhim Zahawi should resign as Conservative Party chairman over his tax controversy. Rishi Sunak is under pressure to fire Zahawi over a multimillion-pound tax dispute.

The Academy announced the 2023 Oscar nominations on Tuesday morning. A24's Everything Everywhere All at Once is the most nominated film with 11 nominations, followed by All Quiet on the Western Front with 9 and The Banshees of Inisherin with 9. The 95th Academy Awards will air on Sunday, March 12, at 8 p.m. ET/5 pm PT on ABC. Jimmy Kimmel will host.

The European Union launched a project to collect and aggregate cancer imaging data in an effort to speed up innovation and early cancer diagnosis using artificial intelligence. The project is in line with the EU's data strategy and compliant with GDPR.

Poland has sent an official request to Germany asking for permission to send tanks to Ukraine. Since the tanks are manufactured in Germany, it must provide permission for their re-export. The German economy ministry confirmed that the necessary coordination and procedures in the German government are ongoing.

The final four of the NFL playoffs are set. Cincinnati Bengals and Kansas City Chiefs will play for the AFC championship. Philadelphia Eagles and San Francisco 49ers will play on the NFC side of the playoffs.

Xylem will buy Evoqua Water Technologies for $7.5 billion in an all-stock deal. The deal is expected to close mid-year and is subject to shareholder approval. The company has been looking for a deal in the water industry for a while.
A white rhino was born at Colchester Zoo on 13 January. The baby is now 10 days old and is running around her enclosure.

Tyre Nichols died on Jan. 10, three days after he was stopped by Memphis police for reckless driving. He was taken into custody after two "confrontations" with officers. His family's attorneys say he was beaten by police. The video of the incident has not been released to the public yet.

The FBI confirms that the Lazarus Group and APT38 are responsible for the theft of $100 million worth of virtual currency from the Harmony Protocol on June 24 last year. The money was laundered for North Korea's ballistic and weapons of mass destruction program.

Sami Zayn takes on Kevin Owens for Roman Reigns at all costs on SmackDown tonight at 8/7 C on FOX.

Novak Djokovic has been accused of faking his injury at the Australian Open. He won his 25th match at the Grand Slam on Monday despite a hamstring injury. He was deported on the eve of the last year's tournament in Melbourne. Victoria Azarenka was questioned over her 10-minute timeout for a rib injury in the 2013 Australian Open semifinal match.

Ernest John Obiena, Kristina Marie Knott, Sarah Dequinan, Hokett delos Santos, Mark Harry Diones, Janry Ubas, and lady pole vaulter Natalie Uy will take part in the Asian Indoor Athletics Championships in Astana, Kazakhstan from February 10 to 12. The competition will be a sneak peek of how the national athletics squad would perform in the Southeast Asian Games and Asian Games this year.

Damar Hamlin collapsed due to cardiac arrest during a football game in Cincinnati earlier this month. Football safety is a topic of debate at the professional and youth levels. Participation in 11-player tackle football has declined 12.2% since the peak in 2008-09.

Jokin Aperribay is the president of La Real Sociedad. He has taken the club out of financial ruin and out of the second division. La Real last won Spain's top division in 1982. They moved to the Anoeta stadium, which has been transformed into Reale Arena. Their youth academy has been very successful.

Twins acquire Michael A. Taylor from Royals for two prospects. Left-handed pitcher Evan Sisk and right-handed Steven Cruz go to Kansas City as part of the deal. To make room for Taylor on the 40-man roster, the Twins designated reliever A.J. Alexy for assignment.

Breanna Stewart wants to help subsidize charter travel for the entire WNBA by contributing profits from her name, image and likeness deals. WNBA does not allow charter flights for its franchises. Commissioner Cathy Engelbert has said it would cost the league $20 million each season to have every team fly privately. Brittney Griner was detained in Russia last year.

Everton have sacked manager Frank Lampard after a run of nine defeats in 12 games. The team is in the Premier League relegation zone and two points from safety. Everton are considering Nuno Espirito Santo, Marcelo Bielsa and Ralph Hasenhuttl as a replacement.

Bill O'Brien will be the new offensive coordinator for the New England Patriots. He was on Bill Belichick's staff from 2007-11. He will take over play-calling duties from Matt Patricia, who will be replaced in 2022. He also worked for the Alabama Crimson Tide under Nick Saban.

Canada won 13 medals at the 2023 FISU Winter World University Games in Lake Placid. It's the second-best Canadian result in the history of the competition. Shilo Rousseau collected two golds and one silver medal. David La Rue was the star of the show, joining Rousseau as the only three-time medallist.

Mundt played in all 17 games during the 2022 regular season for the Vikings. He caught 19 of 21 targets for 140 yards and a touchdown. The 28-year-old also accumulated more receptions and receiving yards than he did in his first six seasons with the Rams.

Tom Brady is taking it a day at a time when it comes to his future in the NFL. The 45-year-old quarterback and his Tampa Bay Buccaneers lost their Wild Card playoff game against the Dallas Cowboys last week. Brady is a free agent.

Thiago Almada became the first active MLS player to win the World Cup in Qatar. MLS had the most rostered players (36) of any league outside the top five and a player on the winning team for the first time in league history. John Thorrington played soccer competitively for Manchester United at the age of 14. He is co-president and general manager of LAFC, which featured five players at World Cup.

Bellator MMA has five events scheduled for the first half of the year. The showcase event on CBS will be the first MMA event to air on CBS since Strikeforce Nashville in 2010. Ryan Bader will put his heavyweight crown on the line against legend Fedor Emelianenko. The card will also feature a middleweight title bout when champion Johnny Eblen takes on top contender Anatoly Tokov. In February, welterweight champion Yaroslav Amosov returns to take on interim titleholder Logan Storley.
There were many wrestling tournaments taking place in New Jersey this weekend. Below we pick one wrestler from each league who shined in the last week.
Ezekiel Elliott is willing to take a pay cut from his current $10.9 million salary to keep playing for the Dallas Cowboys. The team could release him outright or restructure his contract to keep him.

Minnesota Twins have acquired Michael A. Taylor from the Kansas City Royals in exchange for two relief pitching prospects. The 31-year-old center fielder is a Gold Glove winner in his first season with the Royals. He was drafted by the Washington Nationals in 2009.

Canada finished fourth at the Women's Rugby World Cup in November. Rugby Canada is presenting its high-performance plans to World Rugby with a special focus on the women's program. The Canadian women are currently ranked fourth in the world behind No. 1 England, No. 2 New Zealand and No. 3 France. The men's team failed to qualify for the 2023 World Cup. World Rugby has announced plans for the WXV, a new three-tier annual global competition.

ECHO won the M4 Championship Grand Finals in Jakarta, Indonesia. They defeated Blacklist International 4-0 in a best-of-seven series. They used the Ultimate Bonding Experience (UBE) strategy to win the game.

Jimmy Butler has been seeing double teams since Friday night's loss to Dallas Mavericks. The Heat have to find a way to get Butler easy buckets. Opponents are also crowding center Bam Adebayo more often in the post.

The 2023 Farmers Insurance Open starts Wednesday at Torrey PGA Tour's North Course and South Course. World No. 3 Jon Rahm is the tournament's main attraction. Will Zalatoris, Xander Schauffele, Max Homa, Collin Morikawa, Justin Thomas, Hideki Matsuyama, Tony Finau and more are also in the field.

The Boston Celtics have the best record in the NBA this season and are considered the favorites to win the NBA championship. Jayson Tatum, Jaylen Brown, Malcolm Brogdon, Al Horford and Joe Mazzulla's team are winning close games in the last five minutes. Last season, the Celtics were last in the league in clutch games, but this season they have won 15 of them.

Buffalo Bills lost 27-10 to the Cincinnati Bengals in a playoff game on Sunday. Stefon Diggs was seen leaving the locker room early after the game and confronting his teammates on the sidelines. He was eventually stopped from leaving the stadium by practice squad member Duke Johnson. Diggs took to Twitter to respond to the criticism of his actions after the loss.
Gilgeous-Alexander leads Oklahoma City into matchup against Atlanta. The Thunder won the last matchup 121-114 on Dec. 6. Chet Holmgren is out for the season.

Ryan Reynolds has donated £1,600 to children's football team FC United of Wrexham. He is a co-owner of the team with Rob McElhenney. Kayleigh Barton's son Keegan, 11, plays in the under-12s team. She set up a GoFundMe page asking for £480 for the uniforms. Ryan donated £600 first, followed by an extra £1000 and messaged the team's founder Andrew Ruscoe.

Money In The Bank will take place at The O2 in London on July 1, 2023. It will be the first WWE Premium Live Event to be held in London in over two decades. It follows the success of Cardiff’s Clash At The Castle in September 2022, the first major WWE stadium show in the UK since 1992.

Krug has been activated off injured reserve ahead of Tuesday's game against the Sabres. He's been absent for 13 games with a lower-body injury. Krug is expected to play on the third pairing and the No. 1 power-play unit.

Giants offensive coordinator Mike Kafka is getting a second interview with the Houston Texans for their head coaching job. The Colts and Panthers also interviewed him as part of their head coach searches. The Giants' offense improved significantly under Kafka and first-year head coach Brian Daboll.

CBS Sports begins its 66th consecutive season covering the PGA Tour with only its fifth lead analyst in Trevor Immelman. This will be his first full season as a lead analyst. For the first time, CBS will have the entire FedEx Cup playoffs as part of an alternating schedule with NBC. Justin Thomas wants to read a book a month for the year. APGA returns this week with the Farmers Insurance Invitational.
Patrick Mahomes has a high ankle sprain. He is expected to play in the AFC Championship Game against the Cincinnati Bengals on Sunday.
St George-Illawarra Dragons have re-signed prop Blake Lawrie through to the end of the 2026 season. Lawrie made his debut in 2017 and has played 103 games in the Red V.

The Miami Dolphins fired Josh Boyer, their defensive coordinator, on Thursday. Anthony Campanile and Sean Desai are the first two candidates the team is interested in interviewing. Desai has to be requested for an interview through the Seattle Seahawks. Minnesota Vikings have also requested to interview Desai. Washington Commanders are interviewing Dolphins running backs coach Eric Studesville for their offensive coordinator opening.

CBS Sports begins its 66th consecutive year covering the PGA Tour. It starts in prime time on Saturday night from Torrey Pines. For the first time, CBS will have the entire FedEx Cup playoffs as part of an alternating schedule with NBC. Trevor Immelman takes over for Nick Faldo as the new lead analyst. Justin Thomas wants to read a book a month. APGA returns this week with the Farmers Insurance Invitational.

Gareth Bale will play in the AT&T Pebble Beach Pro-Am golf event starting on February 2 in California. The former Real Madrid forward announced his retirement from football earlier this month. He won 22 trophies in his career including five Champions League titles with Madrid and the MLS cup with Los Angeles FC.

Bulls face the Pacers, aim for 4th straight victory. Chicago won the last meeting 124-109 on October 27. Indiana allows 116.8 points per game and has been outscored by 1.8 per game. The Bulls are 5-3 against Central Division teams.
George Kittle is one of the best tight ends in the NFL.

Chelsea are preparing an offer to sign Lyon's Malo Gusto. The right-back has already signed a six-and-a-half year deal with the club and wants to move to Stamford Bridge. Lyon will try to take him back on loan until the end of the season, but Chelsea want him to join them in January.

Victoria Azarenka beats Jessica Pegula 6-4, 6-1 in the quarterfinals of the Australian Open. Azarenko won the 2012 and 2013 championships in Melbourne. She will play Elena Rybakina in the semifinals, who beat Jelena Ostapenko.

Washington Wizards have acquired guard Kendrick Nunn and three future second round picks from the Los Angeles Lakers. They also sent Rui Hachimura to the Lakers. Nunn is a 6'3 point guard who comes off the bench for the Lakers this season. Hachuro was General Manager Tommy Sheppard's first first-round pick. The Wizards did not extend his contract.
